,Recommended,297720,17775284,"Posted: 29 August, 2015",all,Eldercat,"This is a game about being away from your family for work. A parallel commentary from the in game character and the Game Designer. (One of the Game Designer's family plays the family of the protagonist in game)  I beat the game in right about 5 hours. No crashes or glitches. My wife watched me play and she and I both really felt the emotional impact moments from the game. I thought there were spots for some achievements, but maybe not many. The game starts out as a straightforward mystery, and then takes a turn to the surreal. This is more of a game to inspire contemplation rather than wrap everything up nicely. Most of the progression on the mystery is done via optional objectives, and if you don't do them you will be totally lost at the end. If you do all of the optional objectives the message of the game is deceptively easy to understand and only obfuscated by the preconceptions that you bring. Good game. Surreal ending, but good game."
