,Recommended,297720,19070643,"Posted: 14 November, 2015",all,markzwaan,"When 'Lifeless Planet' was anounced about a year ago I was very excited. Exploring an alien planet in a realistic setting sounded like a great premise. Unfortunately the game turned out to be a platformer with a largely empty environments. I also experienced a game breaking bug about 90% through which meant I couldn't finish it.Corpse of Discovery delivers where Lifeless Planet failed. Its environments are much larger and more interesting and the exploring is about discovery and not about quick, carefully timed jumps from platform to platform. It's story is completely different and for a long time I was left wondering in which direction it would go. The graphics aren't perfect (many tufts of grass hovering in mid air in some levels) but I haven't experienced any significant slow downs and the game never crashed.The premise of the game is that you are an astronaut who wakes up in a research lab on an alien planet. Your shuttle has crashed and the chances of you surviving are slim. After watching a message from your family you get your assignment and head out of the airlock. After completing your objective everything turns to black and you awake in the same room. This happens again and again. Is it all a dream, is this a virtual experience, is it a psychological test of the CoD or is there something else going on entirely? Much is left up to you, the player, to figure out which might not be everyones cup of tea. But at about three hours of play time it never drags on and I quite enjoyed it. If you can get it on a discount you won't be disappointed."
