,Recommended,297720,22626176,"Posted: 25 April, 2016",all,Emperor Emblem,"This is an interesting walking sim with some platforming elements. The game intially grabs the player quite well thanks to its Groundhog's Day/All You Need is Kill vibe that it starts out with, and its rather depressing narrative keeps the player at least somewhat interested as to what exactly is going on with the player character.Sadly the game lacks innovation in its own mechanics, and the narrative, although interesting, isn't really directly present until the last two sections of the game. During the time between the initial grab at the player attention and the entertaining, albeit sad conclusion, there is very little keeping the player going outside of the hope for answers. The world building present throughout the game is kept rather minimal, whether this was to keep the narrative as the focus and allow for theorizing, or just lazy game design is up to the player to decide.All in all I'd have to say that the game is interesting enough for me to validate a $5 purchase (the price which I originally bought the game at), but it's best to keep in mind that there is next to no replayability unless you are some kind of theorist fanatic or have a friend sit down and play it while you look for their thoughts and reactions.TL;DRThe game is worth a $5 purchase for those looking for a short (approximately 3 hour) walking sim with an interesting, albeit depressing narrative, and aren't looking for games with replayability in mind.I give it a weird black creature/an entertaining AI Dialogue."
